==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Close-fights
<hw>Close"-fights`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>Barriers with loopholes, formerly erected on the
deck of a vessel to shelter the men in a close engagement with an
enemy's boarders; -- called also <altname>close
quarters</altname>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Closefisted</ent>⟦br⟧
